# ==============================================================================
# AVD-KSV-0109: ArgoCD ConfigMaps reference secret names, not values
# ==============================================================================
# Finding: ConfigMap stores secrets in key(s) or value(s)
# Severity: HIGH
#
# Affected Components:
# - argocd-cm: ArgoCD core configuration
# - argocd-notifications-cm: Notifications configuration
#
# Justification:
# False positive - these ConfigMaps contain references to Kubernetes Secret names
# (e.g., "passwordSecret", "usernameSecret", "token"), not actual secret values.
# ArgoCD follows Kubernetes best practices by storing credentials in Secrets and
# only referencing the Secret names in ConfigMaps.
#
# Example from argocd-cm:
#   dex.config: |
#     connectors:
#     - type: ldap
#       config:
#         bindPW: $dex.ldap.bindPW  # References secret, doesn't contain password
#         passwordSecret: argocd-ldap-password  # Secret name reference
#
# Upstream Issue:
# - https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/discussions/6158
# - https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/issues/16915
#
# Risk Assessment: FALSE POSITIVE (upstream manifest design)
# Review: When upgrading ArgoCD (may be fixed in newer versions)
# Owner: @platform-team
# ==============================================================================
AVD-KSV-0109: argocd-install.yaml
AVD-KSV-0109: gcp-production-app.yaml
